name: 6-[bis(5-ethylfuran-2-yl)methyl]-7-nitro-2,3-dihydro-1,4-benzodioxine
source: Karthikeyan M.; Glen R.C.; Bender A. General melting point prediction based on a diverse compound dataset and artificial neural networks. J. Chem. Inf. Model.; 2005; 45(3); 581-2671
Reason: The molecular structure of 6-[bis(5-ethylfuran-2-yl)methyl]-7-nitro-2,3-dihydro-1,4-benzodioxine consists of a furan ring, a nitro functional group, and an ethyl group. The melting point of the base structure, 2,3-dihydro-1,4-benzodioxine, is approximately -10.5 degrees Celsius. The furan ring contributes to the melting point due to its planarity and increased molecular weight. The nitro functional group also raises the melting point due to its polarity and increased molecular weight. The ethyl group adds steric bulk and increases the molecular weight, which can also contribute to the melting point. The presence of two nitro functional groups can also increase the melting point due to their polarity and increased molecular weight.
